data.description: Bring the horses, goats, ducks and chickens!  With some sweat equity, you can transform this 1965 home & barn into your island dream! This 3 bedroom/1.5 bath home is situated on 4.85 pastoral acres with fenced and cross-fenced grazing fields. An ideal location just down the road to the entrance of the 320 acre Maury Island Marine Park, an island treasure for hiking, biking, horseback riding and beachcoming. The roughed in daylight basement offers 1,010 sq. ft. of possibilities. The barn features a work area, hay storage and two stalls with a fenced paddock with easy access to fenced pastures. Fruit trees dot the eastern portion of the property and big, open skys bathe the property in sunlight. Enjoy nearby Pt. Robinson Lighthouse Park, too!
